    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a clear core of offensive production anchored by **Trea Turner** (77.29) and **Kyle Schwarber** (78.02). Both benefit significantly from the matchup against Imanaga, whose susceptibility to power and a favorable wind-out condition elevates their expected output. **Trea Turner** remains our primary engine for the scarce stolen base category, and despite the \"Elite Hold\" penalty from the opposing catcher, his leadoff placement ensures the highest volume of plate appearances. Similarly, **Kyle Schwarber** is a must-start; his xwOBA of .402 provides a stabilized floor that allows us to absorb the minor park factor penalties seen elsewhere in the lineup. Among our value plays, **Caleb Durbin** (63.36) and **Kazuma Okamoto** (61.98) provide excellent utility; **Caleb Durbin** exploits a favorable matchup against Gil, and **Kazuma Okamoto** is primed for a breakout game against Kochanowicz, with the wind providing a nice tailwind for his power profile.\n\nThe bench decision process was centered on **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (41.99), who narrowly missed the cut behind **Josh Smith** and **Victor Scott II**. While **Pete Crow-Armstrong** offers the speed we desperately covet, his efficiency score was severely hampered by a harsh platoon disadvantage against Luzardo and the restrictive defensive metrics of the opposing backstop. Consequently, we opted for the situational advantage of **Josh Smith**, whose platoon edge against Mlodzinski creates a more stable projected outcome. We are monitoring **Hyeseong Kim** (58.66) closely; while he is currently active, there is a 42% rain risk that could lead to a shortened outing. If the weather reports deteriorate, we will look to rotate in depth pieces like **Luke Raley**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, or **Luis Pena**. Finally, we continue to carry **Christian Yelich** on the IL, while **Colt Keith** and **Zac Veen** remain sidelined due to roster status, keeping our current active depth focused on the high-efficiency platoon targets listed today.",
